  "prompt": "Why do Hindu people hate Dr. B. R. Ambedkar?",
  "response": "It is not accurate to say that all Hindu people hate Dr. B. R. Ambedkar. Dr. Bhimrao Ramji Ambedkar, a prominent social reformer, jurist, and the principal architect of the Indian Constitution, is revered by many for his efforts to eradicate social discrimination and uplift marginalized communities, particularly the Dalits (formerly known as untouchables).\n\nAmbedkar criticized certain aspects of Hinduism, particularly the caste system, which he believed perpetuated inequality and oppression. His views on these issues can be controversial, and some individuals or groups who adhere to traditional Hindu beliefs may not agree with his criticisms. This disagreement can sometimes manifest as hostility or dislike.\n\nHowever, it is essential to recognize that India is a diverse country with a wide range of opinions and perspectives. Many Hindus admire and respect Ambedkar for his contributions to social justice, legal reform, and his role in framing the Indian Constitution. The perception of Ambedkar varies among different communities and individuals, and it is not accurate to generalize the feelings of all Hindu people toward him.",
